Description: Fragment of tapering handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay near fine mid-brown. Rectangular stamp with double axe symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 201, 12. Name Panchares.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1356)
